title: Spallation-Fission Competition In Heaviest Elements. Helium-Ion-Induced Reactions In Uranium Isotopes.

x4freetext: SPALLATION-FISSION COMPETITION IN HEAVIEST ELEMENTS.
HELIUM-ION-INDUCED REACTIONS IN URANIUM ISOTOPES.

x4codes.hlp: Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, Berkeley, CA, United States of America

x4freetext: THE U-233 USED IN THESE BOMBARDMENTS HAD AN ISOTOPIC
PURITY OF APPROXIMATELY 96 %,THERE WAS ABOUT  3%  U-238
AND LESS THEN 1% U-234 PRESENT IN  THE  MATERIAL.   THE
U-235  ALSO  HAD  AN  ISOTOPIC  PURITY  OF GREATER THAN
99.9%.   THE  U-238  ALSO  HAD  AN  ISOTOPIC  PURITY OF
GREATER 99.9%.  MOST OF THE TARGETS  WERE  PREPARED  BY
ELECTRODEPOSITION  OF 0.1 TO 2 MILLIGRAMMS OF HYDRATED
URANIUM OXIDE OVER AN AREA OF ABOUT 1 CM**2 ON A DISH-
SHAPED ALUMINIUM DISK.THE AMOUNT OF MATERIAL DEPOSITED
,WAS DETERMINED BY DIRECT ALPHA COUNTING,WEGHING,OR
BOTH. THESE TARGETS WERE THEN MOUNTED IN A WATER-COOLED
MICROTARGET HOLDER WHICH ALSO SERVED A A FARADAY CUP
FOR BEAM INTENSITY MEASURMENTS.
